node.title: Homicide investigation into 48yo man's death in Te Awamutu
node.description: Police have launched a homicide investigation over a death at a Te Awamutu property.

node.title: Man exonerated in Malcolm X's murder sues New York state
node.description: Muhammad Aziz is suing the state of New York for at least $20 million.

node.title: Officer Is Charged With Protecting Prostitution Ring in Exchange for Sex
node.description: Prosecutors say Wayne Peiffer, a police officer in Brewster, N.Y., had women from sex-trafficking and prostitution rings brought to him at the police station.

node.title: Judge Dismisses Trump Suit Seeking to Stop Congress From Seeing His Taxes
node.description: The court said the Treasury Department can provide the former president’s tax returns to the House Ways and Means Committee. But the judge stayed the ruling to allow time for an appeal.

node.title: Two Zebras 'Returned to the Herd' After Escaping Maryland Farm in August
node.description: The owner of the farm where the zebras escaped faces three counts of animal neglect, according to authorities.

node.title: Former Interns Say SpaceX Ignored Sexual Harassment
node.description: Some women at the company, founded by Elon Musk, described feelings of powerlessness and a failure by the company’s human resources office to discipline male employees.

node.title: Internet Backs Redditor Who Refuses to Babysit Teenaged Brother After 'Incident'
node.description: "As a fellow oldest child, it's exhausting how we're considered the built-in babysitters," one commenter wrote.

node.title: Virginia Lawmakers Asked to End Grocery Tax By Northam, After GOP Successor Ran on Idea
node.description: Glenn Youngkin, who is scheduled to take office in mid-January, has said that the tax is regressive and disproportionately affects low-income people.

node.title: Tasmanian author tops $80,000 Prime Minister’s Literary Awards, following Miles Franklin win
node.description: Tasmanian author Amanda Lohrey has won the $80,000 Prime Minister's Literary Award for her seventh novel, The Labyrinth — compounding a banner year in which she also won the $60,000 Miles Franklin Literary Award.

node.title: Man accused murdering Lena Zhang Harrap declared fit to stand trial
node.description: The man charged with murdering Auckland woman Lena Zhang Harrap has been found fit to stand trial.

node.title: Auckland border testing may only catch a quarter of cases - govt report
node.description: Government officials think the testing requirement to leave Auckland from today might only catch a quarter of the number of Covid-19 cases leaving.
